question:
District category contains Historic Downtown, Condo District, and School District.
Supermarkets category contains Tesco, Hannaford, and Sprouts Farmers Market.
Product category contains Cheese Puffs, Half-and-half, and Potato Chips.
The number of each Condo District 's Hannaford equals 16 times the sum of each Hannaford 's Half-and-half and each Tesco 's Product.
The number of each Hannaford 's Cheese Puffs equals 7.
The number of each Tesco 's Cheese Puffs equals each Tesco 's Half-and-half.
The number of each Condo District 's Sprouts Farmers Market equals 17 more than each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Product.
The number of each Hannaford 's Half-and-half equals 17 more than each Hannaford 's Cheese Puffs.
The number of each School District 's Tesco equals the sum of each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Half-and-half and each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Product.
The number of each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Half-and-half equals 17.
The number of each Historic Downtown 's Tesco equals 18 more than each Condo District 's Sprouts Farmers Market.
The number of each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Cheese Puffs equals 17.
The number of each Tesco 's Half-and-half equals 1 more than each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Cheese Puffs.
The number of each Condo District 's Tesco equals each Historic Downtown 's Product.
How many Product does Historic Downtown have?
solution:
Define each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Cheese Puffs as K; So K = 17.
Define each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Half-and-half as G; So G = 17.
Define each Sprouts Farmers Market 's Product as I; So I = K + G = 17 + 17 = 11.
Define each Condo District 's Sprouts Farmers Market as J; So J = 17 + I = 17 + 11 = 5.
Define each Tesco 's Half-and-half as N; So N = 1 + K = 1 + 17 = 18.
Define each Historic Downtown 's Tesco as v; So v = 18 + J = 18 + 5 = 0.
Define each Tesco 's Cheese Puffs as a; So a = N = 18.
Define each Tesco 's Product as r; So r = N + a = 18 + 18 = 13.
Define each Historic Downtown 's Product as Q; Q = v * r = 0 * 13 = 0.
